TITLE: Louisiana Gov. Landry issues disaster declaration amid crawfish shortage
SUMMARY: Republican Louisiana Gov. Jeff Landry on Wednesday issued a disaster declaration for the crawfish industry, citing an ongoing shortage.

TITLE: Trump campaign rejects effort to have RNC foot former president's legal bills: 'Hard no'
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump's campaign is rejecting an effort to get the Republican National Committee to cover the legal bills associated with his pending criminal cases.

TITLE: White House calls on world leaders to help stop 'reckless' Houthi attacks after civilian sailors killed
SUMMARY: The White House condemned a Houthis missile attack on the bulk carrier ship True Confidence on Wednesday, which resulted in three fatalities and at least four others getting injured.

TITLE: Former Virginia delegate acquitted of felony charges in hit-and-run case
SUMMARY: Republican former Virginia lawmaker Matt Fariss has been acquitted of felony hit-and-run and malicious wounding charges over a conflict with his ex-girlfriend.

TITLE: ICE catches Guatemalan illegal immigrant convicted of child sex offense who was released in Virginia
SUMMARY: Federal immigration authorities have announced the capture of an illegal immigrant convicted of a child sex offense, but who was later put back out onto the streets.

TITLE: Laken Riley's parents won't be at Biden's State of the Union, will grieve loss from home: Rep. Mike Collins
SUMMARY: The parents of Laken Riley, the Georgia nursing student allegedly killed by an illegal immigrant, will not attend the State of the Union on Thursday.

TITLE: On the eve of the State of the Union address, President Biden is struggling — with his own party
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden is looking to gain back the trust of the Democratic voting base after his lackluster performance in Super Tuesday's voting.

TITLE: Senate Commerce Republicans expand probe into airports in ‘sanctuary’ jurisdictions sheltering migrants
SUMMARY: Republicans on the Senate Commerce Committee are investigating the sheltering of migrants at airports in "sanctuary" jurisdictions, as the crisis grips the country.

TITLE: Nathan Wade's phone data shows he made midnight trips to Fani Willis' condo before he was hired: attorney
SUMMARY: Attorney Ashleigh Merchant testified Wednesday in a Georgia state senate hearing that special prosecutor Nathan Wade's cellphone data shows 1 a.m. trips to Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis' home prior to his hiring.

TITLE: Karine Jean-Pierre says Biden is ready to handle hecklers during State of the Union: 'He got this'
SUMMARY: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre told reporters on Wednesday that President Biden will be prepared to handle hecklers during the State of the Union on Thursday night.

SUMMARY: Sen. Joni Ernst, R-Iowa, attempted to force a floor vote on a bill that would require ICE to take custody of illegal immigrants who are arrested for the death or injury of another person.

SUMMARY: The latest updates from the 2024 campaign trail, exclusive interviews and more Fox News politics content

SUMMARY: Sheriff Greg Capers of San Jacinto County, Texas, has lost his bid for a fourth term in office. Capers was heavily scrutinized last year for his response to a mass shooting.

SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump is calling for debates between himself and President Biden ahead of the 2024 general election, saying he is willing to participate "anytime, anywhere, anyplace."

TITLE: Florida bill banning homeless encampments on public property heads to DeSantis' desk
SUMMARY: Florida is set to ban thousands of homeless residents from sleeping or establishing camps on public property under a bill passed by the Legislature and supported by Gov. Ron DeSantis.

SUMMARY: Democratic Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers on Wednesday signed a bill allowing hundreds of millions of dollars in spending on Universities of Wisconsin-related construction projects.

SUMMARY: FIRST ON FOX: House Speaker Mike Johnson launched a fundraising hub in an effort to grow the Republicans’ majority in the House in 2024 following former President Trump’s Super Tuesday wins.

TITLE: Democratic Illinois 'super mayor' vetoes attempt to probe her lavish spending
SUMMARY: Self-described Illinois "super mayor" Tiffany Henyard has vetoed a resolution by a local board that called for an external probe to be launched into her alleged misuse of funds.

TITLE: Supreme Court to hear arguments in Trump presidential immunity case on April 25
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court will hear arguments on the question of whether former President Trump is immune from prosecution in Special Counsel Jack Smith’s election interference case on April 25.

TITLE: Blue state legislature passes parents’ bill of rights, critic calls it a ‘right-wing hot air’ balloon

TITLE: Comer invites Hunter Biden, business associates to testify publicly March 20 amid impeachment inquiry

TITLE: Sen. Joni Ernst becomes final member of Senate GOP leadership to endorse Trump
SUMMARY: Sen. Joni Ernst becomes last member of the GOP leadership conference to endorse former President Donald Trump ahead of the 2024 General Election.
